      "Bash(/tmp/stratum_query_capabilities.md << 'EOF'\n# Stratum Query Execution Capabilities - Complete Analysis\n\n## Project Overview\nStratum is a columnar analytics engine for Clojure with:\n- SIMD-accelerated query execution via JDK Vector API\n- Hash-based joins\n- Fused filter+aggregate operations\n- Zone map-aware predicate pushdown\n- Late materialization via SelectionVectors\n- SQL interface via PostgreSQL wire protocol\n\n**Total source code:** ~14K LOC \\(main query engine: 5,648 lines\\)\n\n---\n\n## 1. WINDOW FUNCTIONS\n\n### Status: PARTIAL SUPPORT\n**Limited to rolling/fixed-window operations, NOT SQL window semantics**\n\n#### Implemented:\n- **Rolling Window** \\(`idx-rolling-window` in compute.clj:583-597\\)\n  - Fixed-size sliding windows over ordered data\n  - Supports multiple edge modes: `:center`, `:clamp`\n  - Returns new index with window results\n  - Delegates to dtype-next rolling operations\n  \n- **Ranking** \\(`idx-rank` in compute.clj:542-553\\)\n  - Computes rank of each element \\(0-based, ascending\\)\n  - Simple argsort-based implementation\n  - Not PARTITION BY-aware \\(no per-group ranking\\)\n  - No ROW_NUMBER, DENSE_RANK, RANK variants\n\n- **Cumulative Operations**\n  - `idx-cumsum` \\(compute.clj:599-605\\) — Cumulative sum\n  - Delegates to dtype-next cfn/cumsum\n  - No other cumulative functions \\(cummax, cummin\\)\n\n#### NOT Supported:\n- `ROW_NUMBER\\(\\) OVER \\(PARTITION BY ... ORDER BY ...\\)` — NO\n- `RANK\\(\\) / DENSE_RANK\\(\\) OVER \\(...\\)` — NO\n- `LAG\\(\\) / LEAD\\(\\)` — NO\n- `FIRST_VALUE\\(\\) / LAST_VALUE\\(\\)` — NO\n- `NTILE\\(\\)` — NO\n- Frame specifications \\(`ROWS BETWEEN ...`\\) — NO\n- Multiple PARTITION BY clauses — NO\n- SQL OVER syntax in general — NO\n\n#### Limitation:\nThese functions are available only in the Clojure API for low-level rolling operations, NOT exposed through SQL. The SQL parser \\(sql.clj\\) has **zero support** for window function syntax. Documentation explicitly lists \"Window functions\" as unsupported SQL \\(doc/sql-interface.md:185\\).\n\n---\n\n## 2. SUBQUERIES & CTEs\n\n### Status: NOT IMPLEMENTED\n\n#### What's Missing:\n- **Subqueries**: `WHERE col IN \\(SELECT ...\\)` — NOT parsed\n- **Correlated Subqueries**: `WHERE ... \\(SELECT ... WHERE outer.id = inner.id\\)` — NOT parsed\n- **CTEs \\(Common Table Expressions\\)**: `WITH cte AS \\(SELECT ...\\) SELECT * FROM cte` — NOT parsed\n- **Set Operations**: `UNION`, `INTERSECT`, `EXCEPT` — NOT supported\n\n#### Evidence:\n1. SQL parser \\(sql.clj\\) only imports `PlainSelect` from JSqlParser, no handling for:\n   - `WithClause` or `CTE`\n   - `SetOperation` \\(union, intersect, except\\)\n   - Nested `ParenthesizedSelect` in predicates\n\n2. JSqlParser AST node handling \\(sql.clj:952-989\\):\n   ```clojure\n   ;; Only handles PlainSelect at top level\n   \\(when \\(instance? PlainSelect stmt\\) ...\\)\n   \\(else {:error \"Unsupported SQL statement type: \" \\(type stmt\\)}\\)\n   ```\n   No `With` statement handling.\n\n3. FROM clause only accepts:\n   - `Table` nodes \\(e.g., `orders`, `read_csv\\('file.csv'\\)`\\)\n   - NOT `Select` or `ParenthesizedSelect`\n\n4. Documented as \"Not Supported\" \\(doc/sql-interface.md:183-185\\):\n   ```\n   | Subqueries | WHERE x IN \\(SELECT ...\\) |\n   | CTEs \\(WITH\\) | WITH t AS \\(SELECT ...\\) |\n   ```\n\n---\n\n## 3. ORDER BY / LIMIT / SORTING\n\n### Status: FULLY SUPPORTED\n\n#### Implemented:\n\n**ORDER BY** \\(`apply-order` in query.clj:4570-4590\\):\n```clojure\n:order [[:region :desc] [:amount :asc]]  ;; Multi-column sort\n```\n- Multiple sort keys with per-column direction \\(ASC/DESC\\)\n- Comparator composition: try ASC key1, if tied try ASC key2, etc.\n- Uses Clojure's `sort` with multi-key comparator function\n- Post-execution \\(applied after aggregation\\)\n\n**LIMIT** \\(`apply-limit-offset` in query.clj:4592-4598\\):\n```clojure\n:limit 100     ;; Take first N rows\n:offset 50     ;; Skip first N rows\n```\n- Applied via `drop` + `take`\n- Post-execution ordering: LIMIT applied after ORDER BY\n\n**DISTINCT** \\(query.clj:4736-4760\\):\n```clojure\n:distinct true  ;; SELECT DISTINCT\n```\n- Hash-set based deduplication\n- Applied post-aggregation if GROUP BY used\n\n#### SQL Examples:\n```sql\nSELECT region, SUM\\(amount\\) FROM orders \nWHERE price > 100\nGROUP BY region\nHAVING COUNT\\(*\\) > 2\nORDER BY region DESC, sum ASC\nLIMIT 10 OFFSET 5;\n```\n\n#### Limitations:\n- **No Top-N optimization**: Uses full sort, not heap/partial sort\n- **No min-heap for large LIMIT**: Sorts entire result set\n- **No index-based optimization**: Cannot use B-tree indices for ORDER BY\n- **Post-execution only**: Cannot push LIMIT into execution engine for early termination\n\n---\n\n## 4. LATE MATERIALIZATION & COLUMN PRUNING\n\n### Status: PARTIAL SUPPORT \\(Indices only\\)\n\n#### Implemented:\n\n**SelectionVector** \\(compute.clj:29-73\\):\n```clojure\n\\(defprotocol ISelectionVector\n  \\(sel-length [this]\\)\n  \\(sel-indices [this]\\)\n  \\(sel-to-bitmap [this]\\)\n  \\(sel-intersect [this other]\\)\n  \\(sel-union [this other]\\)\n  \\(sel-difference [this other]\\)\\)\n```\n- Represents selected rows as indices or RoaringBitmap\n- Avoids materialization until needed\n- Supports set operations on selections\n\n**Zone Map Pruning** \\(index.clj:976-1017\\):\n- Skips chunks that cannot contain matching values\n- Used in filter operations to avoid materialization\n- Works on indexed columns only \\(PersistentColumnIndex\\)\n- Examples: `idx-filter-range`, `idx-filter-zonemap`\n\n**Index-Aware Materialization** \\(index.clj:1223-1247, `idx-materialize-to-array-pruned`\\):\n```\nZone-map check → Skip entire chunks → Materialize only surviving chunks\n```\n- Reduces memory allocation for filtered queries\n- Documented in query-engine.md:80-81:\n  ```\n  Zone map pruning \\(index inputs\\): Classify chunks as skip/stats-only/SIMD using ChunkStats\n  ```\n\n#### Limited Scope:\n- **Only for indexed inputs** \\(`PersistentColumnIndex`\\), NOT raw arrays\n- **No projection pushdown**: All columns materialized together\n- **No column selection optimization**: If query selects columns A, B but filters on column C, all three still materialized\n- **For array inputs**: No SelectionVector optimization, full materialization always\n\n#### NOT Supported:\n- Projection pushdown at execution engine level\n- Column-by-column lazy loading\n- Columnar storage skipping unused columns\n\n---\n\n## 5. BLOOM FILTERS\n\n### Status: NOT IMPLEMENTED\n\n#### Evidence:\n- Zero mentions of \"bloom\" in entire codebase\n- No BloomFilter class in Java source\n- No predicate pushdown filter structures\n- Only hash tables used for joins \\(not filters\\)\n\n#### Join Implementation \\(query.clj:4799-4890\\):\n- **Hash table probe**: Build hash table on dimension keys, probe with fact keys\n- Simple hash-based, no Bloom pre-filter\n- No false-positive filtering mechanism\n\n---\n\n## COMPREHENSIVE QUERY OPERATOR SUPPORT\n\n### Supported Operators\n\n#### **Filtering/Predicates**:\n- Comparison: `<`, `>`, `<=`, `>=`, `=`, `!=`\n- Range: `BETWEEN lo AND hi`\n- Set membership: `IN \\(val1, val2, ...\\)`\n- String matching: `LIKE 'pattern%'`, `CONTAINS`, `STARTS_WITH`, `ENDS_WITH`\n- NULL checks: `IS NULL`, `IS NOT NULL`\n- Logical: `AND`, `OR`, `NOT`\n- Compiled predicates: Complex OR/IN converted to bytecode masks\n\n#### **Aggregations**:\n- Basic: SUM, COUNT, AVG, MIN, MAX\n- Statistical: STDDEV, STDDEV_POP, STDDEV_SAMP, VARIANCE, VAR_POP, VAR_SAMP\n- Correlation: CORR\\(col1, col2\\)\n- Quantiles: MEDIAN, PERCENTILE_CONT, PERCENTILE_DISC, APPROX_QUANTILE\n- Distinct: COUNT\\(DISTINCT col\\)\n- Compound: SUM\\(col1 * col2\\), SUM\\(col1\\) - MIN\\(col2\\)\n\n#### **Grouping**:\n- GROUP BY \\(single and multiple columns\\)\n- HAVING \\(post-aggregation filtering\\)\n- Dense group-by \\(key space ≤ 100K\\)\n- Partitioned group-by \\(high cardinality via radix partitioning\\)\n- Sparse group-by \\(hash-based for very high cardinality\\)\n\n#### **Joins**:\n- INNER JOIN\n- LEFT JOIN\n- RIGHT JOIN\n- FULL OUTER JOIN\n- Single join with hash table probe\n- Fused join+group-by optimization\n\n#### **Expressions**:\n- Arithmetic: `+`, `-`, `*`, `/`, `%` \\(MOD\\), `**` \\(POWER\\)\n- Math: `ABS`, `SQRT`, `LOG`, `LOG10`, `EXP`, `ROUND`, `FLOOR`, `CEIL`, `SIGN`\n- String: `UPPER`, `LOWER`, `LENGTH`, `SUBSTR`, `REPLACE`, `TRIM`, `CONCAT`\n- Date: `DATE_TRUNC`, `EXTRACT`, `DATE_ADD`, `DATE_DIFF`\n- Type casts: `CAST\\(col AS DOUBLE/LONG/STRING\\)`\n- Conditional: `CASE WHEN ... THEN ... ELSE ...`\n- NULL handling: `COALESCE`, `NULLIF`\n\n#### **Specialized**:\n- Anomaly detection: `ANOMALY_SCORE`, `ANOMALY_PREDICT`, `ANOMALY_PROBA`, `ANOMALY_CONFIDENCE`\n- Rolling windows: Fixed-size sliding windows \\(low-level API only\\)\n- Ranking: `idx-rank` \\(low-level API, not SQL\\)\n\n---\n\n## EXECUTION ENGINE ARCHITECTURE\n\n### Query Dispatch Decision Tree \\(query-engine.md:91-132\\)\n\nThe engine selects the fastest strategy based on query shape:\n\n```\nINPUT\n  ↓\nIs projection-only \\(no agg, no group\\)?\n  → Yes: execute-projection \\(materialize + filter + select\\)\n  → No: continue\n  \nIs fused extract+count \\(EXTRACT expr + COUNT\\)?\n  → Yes: fusedExtractCountDenseParallel \\(Java SIMD\\)\n  → No: continue\n  \nIs input PersistentColumnIndex eligible for chunked group-by?\n  → Yes: execute-chunked-group-by \\(streams over chunks\\)\n  → No: continue\n  \nIs fused join+group-by \\(single INNER, keyword groups, no WHERE\\)?\n  → Yes: fusedJoinGroupAggregateDenseRange \\(Java\\)\n  → No: continue\n  \nIs single agg with ≤4 long + ≤4 double predicates on ≥1000 rows?\n  → Yes: Is it COUNT?\n    → Yes: fusedSimdCountParallel\n    → No: fusedSimdParallel \\(SUM/SUM_PRODUCT/MIN/MAX\\)\n  → No: continue\n  \nAre all aggs SUM/SUM_PRODUCT/COUNT/AVG with ≤4 aggs?\n  → Yes: fusedSimdMultiSumParallel \\(multi-agg SIMD\\)\n  → No: continue\n  \nIs this a group-by?\n  → Yes: Is max key ≤ dense limit \\(100K\\)?\n    → Yes: fusedFilterGroupAggregateDenseParallel \\(dense hash table\\)\n    → No: fusedFilterGroupAggregatePartitioned \\(radix hash with partitioning\\)\n  → No: continue\n  \nIs this percentile/median/approx-quantile?\n  → Yes: Scalar path \\(collect values, QuickSelect or t-digest\\)\n  → No: Fallback \\(N-pass or scalar\\)\n```\n\n### Execution Strategies\n\n#### **1. Fused SIMD Filter+Aggregate** \\(>1000 rows\\)\n- Java method: `fusedSimdParallel`, `fusedSimdCountParallel`\n- Predicates: Separate into long[] and double[] groups\n- Single pass: Filter and aggregate in SIMD loop\n- SIMD lanes: 8 doubles/cycle \\(AVX-512\\), 4 \\(AVX-2\\)\n- Used for: SUM, SUM_PRODUCT, MIN, MAX, COUNT with simple predicates\n\n#### **2. Scalar Fused Filter+Aggregate** \\(<1000 rows\\)\n- Java method: `fusedFilterAggregate`\n- Per-row: Check all predicates \\(with short-circuit\\), accumulate\n- No SIMD overhead\n\n#### **3. Dense Group-By** \\(key space ≤ 100K\\)\n- Java method: `fusedFilterGroupAggregateDenseParallel`\n- Pre-allocates `double[maxKey][2*nAggs]` per thread\n- Direct array indexing \\(no hash table\\)\n- Thread-local accumulators merged at end\n- Supports VARIANCE/CORR \\(requires 2 accumulators per group\\)\n\n#### **4. Partitioned Group-By** \\(high cardinality\\)\n- Java method: `fusedFilterGroupAggregatePartitioned`\n- Radix partitioning on group keys\n- Hash table per partition\n- Parallel across partitions\n\n#### **5. Chunked Group-By** \\(indexed input\\)\n- Streams over chunks of PersistentColumnIndex\n- Avoids full materialization\n- Applies dense group-by per chunk, then merges\n\n#### **6. Projection** \\(SELECT without agg/group\\)\n- Materialize selected columns\n- Apply WHERE predicates\n- Apply SELECT expressions\n- Sort + limit if needed\n\n#### **7. Hash Join**\n- Build hash table on right table \\(dimension keys\\)\n- Probe with left table \\(fact keys\\)\n- Gather matched rows\n- Support fused join+group-by for INNER joins\n\n---\n\n## OPTIMIZATION TECHNIQUES\n\n### Implemented:\n\n1. **Zone Maps** \\(index.clj:814-1017\\)\n   - Per-chunk min/max statistics\n   - Skips chunks outside predicate range\n   - Works with range, GT, LT, EQ predicates\n\n2. **Parallel Execution** \\(query_compiler.clj:204-233\\)\n   - SIMD operations use ForkJoinPool\n   - Parallel threshold: 200K rows \\(tuneable\\)\n   - Separate methods for COUNT \\(JIT isolation\\) vs aggregates\n\n3. **Expression Pre-computation** \\(query.clj:1300+\\)\n   - Expressions evaluated to arrays before filtering\n   - `eval-expr-vectorized`: Vectorized Java array ops\n   - Example: `[:* :price :qty]` → `ColumnOps.arrayMul\\(price, qty, len\\)`\n\n4. **Dictionary Encoding** \\(query.clj:1700+\\)\n   - String columns encoded as long[] codes\n   - Enables direct array indexing in group-by\n   - Pre-encoding critical \\(3-4x overhead per-query\\)\n\n5. **Compiled Predicate Masks** \\(query.clj:2400+\\)\n   - Complex predicates \\(OR, IN\\) compiled to bytecode\n   - `[:or [:< :a 5] [:> :b 10]]` → compiled mask array\n   - Passed as `[:__mask :eq 1]` to SIMD\n\n6. **Multi-Agg Vectorization** \\(query_compiler.clj:prepare-aggregation\\)\n   - `fusedSimdMultiSumParallel`: Up to 4 aggs in single SIMD pass\n   - Avoids N-pass execution\n\n7. **Columnar Output** \\(query.clj:3900+\\)\n   - `:result :columns` returns `{:col1 array :col2 array ...}`\n   - 15x faster for high-cardinality group-by\n   - Skips per-row map creation\n\n### NOT Implemented:\n\n1. **Predicate Pushdown** — No push into I/O layer\n2. **Projection Pushdown** — All columns materialized together\n3. **Bloom Filters** — No false-positive filtering\n4. **Adaptive Query Execution** — No runtime plan adjustment\n5. **Partial Sort** \\(Top-N heap\\) — Full sort always\n6. **Materialized Views** — No caching of intermediate results\n7. **Query Caching** — No memoization of identical queries\n8. **Batch Processing** — Single query at a time\n9. **Spill-to-Disk** — Out-of-core not supported\n10. **Histogram Equi-Join Optimization** — No histogram-based histogram joins\n\n---\n\n## QUERY EXECUTION PIPELINE\n\n### Sequential Steps \\(query.clj:5064+, execute function\\):\n\n1. **prepare-columns**: Resolve `:from` data, detect types \\(long[], double[], dict-encoded\\)\n2. **Join execution**: If `:join` present, build hash tables, probe, gather matched rows\n3. **Expression pre-computation**: Evaluate WHERE/AGG/GROUP/SELECT expressions to arrays\n4. **Zone map pruning**: Classify index chunks as skip/stats-only/SIMD\n5. **Predicate separation**: Split into long/double groups, compile complex predicates\n6. **Dispatch**: Route to optimal strategy based on query shape\n7. **Result decode**: Convert Java arrays to Clojure maps or columnar format\n8. **Post-processing**: Apply HAVING, ORDER BY, LIMIT, OFFSET, DISTINCT\n\n---\n\n## SQL PARSER CAPABILITIES \\(sql.clj\\)\n\n### Supported Clauses:\n- SELECT \\(with aliases, expressions, aggregates\\)\n- FROM \\(table name, read_csv\\(\\), read_parquet\\(\\)\\)\n- WHERE \\(predicates with AND/OR/NOT, comparison ops, IN, BETWEEN, LIKE, IS NULL\\)\n- GROUP BY \\(columns, expressions, positional references\\)\n- HAVING \\(post-agg filtering\\)\n- ORDER BY \\(multi-column, ASC/DESC\\)\n- LIMIT / OFFSET\n- DISTINCT\n- JOIN \\(INNER, LEFT, RIGHT, FULL\\)\n\n### NOT Supported:\n- Subqueries in WHERE/FROM\n- CTEs \\(WITH clause\\)\n- Window functions \\(ROW_NUMBER, etc.\\)\n- Set operations \\(UNION, INTERSECT\\)\n- DDL \\(CREATE TABLE\\)\n- DML \\(INSERT, UPDATE, DELETE\\)\n\n### System Queries:\n- SET, SHOW, RESET, BEGIN, COMMIT, ROLLBACK\n- DISCARD, LISTEN, UNLISTEN, DEALLOCATE, CLOSE\n- VERSION\\(\\), CURRENT_DATABASE\\(\\), CURRENT_SCHEMA\\(\\), CURRENT_USER\\(\\)\n- pg_catalog queries \\(returns empty\\)\n\n---\n\n## PERFORMANCE CHARACTERISTICS\n\n### Benchmarks \\(bench/olap_bench.clj\\):\n\n**Tier 1 \\(TPC-H\\)**:\n- B1: TPC-H Q6 on 6M rows — ~16.2ms \\(Stratum\\) vs 19.5ms \\(DuckDB\\)\n- B2: TPC-H Q1 \\(complex agg + group-by\\)\n- B3: SSB Q1.1 \\(multi-table, 60M rows\\)\n\n**Tier 2 \\(H2O db-benchmark\\)**:\n- Q1-Q10: Various filter+group-by patterns\n\n**Tier 3 \\(ClickBench numeric subset\\)**:\n- Q19, Q43, etc.\n\n**Tier 4 \\(NYC Taxi\\)**:\n- Real-world analytical queries\n\n**Tier 5 \\(Hash Joins\\)**:\n- Single-table and multi-table joins\n\n**Tier 6 \\(Statistical Aggregates\\)**:\n- MEDIAN, PERCENTILE, APPROX_QUANTILE\n\n### Parallelization:\n- Default: Parallel for ≥200K rows\n- Threshold tuneable: `\\(ColumnOps/setParallelThreshold n\\)`\n- Single-threaded variant: `:bench-1t` in benchmarks\n\n---\n\n## KEY LIMITATIONS & GAPS\n\n### Critical Gaps:\n\n1. **NO Window Functions** \\(SQL-level\\)\n   - No PARTITION BY / ORDER BY OVER clause\n   - Only low-level rolling window API \\(not public SQL\\)\n\n2. **NO Subqueries / CTEs**\n   - Cannot compose queries\n   - No query reuse patterns\n\n3. **NO Top-N / Partial Sort**\n   - Slow for large results with small LIMIT\n   - No heap-based optimization\n\n4. **NO Bloom Filters**\n   - Join optimization missing\n   - No false-positive filtering\n\n5. **NO Advanced Materialization**\n   - Only SelectionVector on indexed inputs\n   - No lazy column access on arrays\n\n6. **NO Spill-to-Disk**\n   - Out-of-core queries fail\n   - Memory-bound\n\n7. **Limited to Single Query Execution**\n   - No parallel query processing\n   - No interleaved multi-query execution\n\n### Design Constraints:\n\n- **Array-based**: Assumes all data fits in memory as Java arrays\n- **Hash-based**: Uses hash tables for joins/group-by, not merge-join\n- **Single-pass**: Can't re-materialize columns \\(expression pre-computation immutable\\)\n- **JVM-bound**: Depends on JDK Vector API \\(requires `--add-modules jdk.incubator.vector`\\)\n\n---\n\n## SUMMARY TABLE\n\n| Feature | Status | Notes |\n|---------|--------|-------|\n| **Window Functions** | PARTIAL | Rolling windows \\(low-level API only\\), idx-rank, cumsum; NO SQL OVER syntax |\n| **Subqueries** | NO | No IN \\(SELECT...\\), no nested SELECTs |\n| **CTEs \\(WITH\\)** | NO | No common table expressions |\n| **ORDER BY** | YES | Multi-column sort, ASC/DESC |\n| **LIMIT/OFFSET** | YES | Post-execution, full sort needed |\n| **Sorting Optimization** | NO | No min-heap, no index-based sort |\n| **Late Materialization** | PARTIAL | SelectionVector on indices; no column pruning on arrays |\n| **Column Pruning** | NO | All columns materialized together |\n| **Bloom Filters** | NO | No false-positive filtering |\n| **Zone Map Pruning** | YES | Skips chunks outside predicate range |\n| **Fused Filter+Aggregate** | YES | Single-pass SIMD on simple queries |\n| **GROUP BY** | YES | Dense \\(≤100K\\) and partitioned high-cardinality |\n| **JOINs** | YES | INNER, LEFT, RIGHT, FULL with hash probe |\n| **Statistical Aggs** | YES | MEDIAN, PERCENTILE, APPROX_QUANTILE |\n| **Anomaly Detection** | YES | Isolation forest scoring |\n| **Predicate Pushdown** | PARTIAL | Zone maps only; no join pushdown |\n| **Projection Pushdown** | NO | All columns materialized |\n| **Parallel Execution** | YES | ForkJoinPool for ≥200K rows |\n| **Parallel Queries** | NO | One query at a time |\n| **Out-of-Core** | NO | Memory-bound to array size |\n| **Columnar Output** | YES | `:result :columns` format |\n| **SQL Support** | ~70% | See SQL parser section |\nEOF)",
      "Bash(jar tf:*)",
